<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>MOR/RYDE RUBBER SPRING SUSPENSION - REPLACEMENT - HANGER ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
        <title>HANGER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>As illustrated in
                <hotlnk document="s03009_6.xml" xrefid="f0300904">Figure 4</hotlnk>, the hanger assembly attaches the
                rubber spring assemblies to the chassis side-members and also supports the top of the shock absorbers.
            </para>
            <para>Failure of the hanger assembly is generally the result of the hanger assembly tie straps being loose
                or broken.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the vehicle is elevated, the chassis is supported with safety stands, the
                    front wheels blocked, and the suspension hanging unsupported.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support axle housing with floor jack.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shock absorbers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rubber spring assemblies from the affected hanger assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_6.xml" xrefid="hl0300905">RUBBER SPRINGS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove crossmember straps attached to affected hanger assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_7.xml" xrefid="hl0300906">CROSSMEMBER STRAPS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hanger assembly from chassis sidemember.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before attaching new hanger assembly to chassis side-member, make sure the contact area
                    is clean and free of any foreign material and metal shavings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new hanger assembly on chassis sidemember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reattach crossmember straps. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_7.xml" xrefid="hl0300906">CROSSMEMBER STRAPS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten all hanger assembly bolts first; then tighten crossmember strap bolts. Refer to
                    the
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300901">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall rubber spring assemblies. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_6.xml" xrefid="hl0300905">RUBBER SPRINGS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall shock absorber. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_11.xml" xrefid="hl0300904">SHOCK ABSORBER</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
